<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="description" content="">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

  <!-- Place favicon.ico and apple-touch-icon.png in the root directory -->

  <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway:400,100,300,700,600,500' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Droid+Serif:400,400italic,700' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>

  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Satisfy" rel="stylesheet" />

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
  <title>
    <%= title %>
  </title>
  <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />


</head>

<body>
  <% var data= "homePage" %>
    <% include templates/header.ejs %>

    <!-- Slider Start
        ============================================================== -->

    <section id="slider">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="block">
                        <div class="slider-text-area">
                            <div class="slider-text">
                                <h2>JSON -> Graph. That Simple <br></h2>
                                <br>
                                <p class="sub-slider-text" style="font-size:20px;">Imagine you have a Data set in JSON format, <br/> And wondering how or which graph to plot?<br>No
                                    worry, We do that for you. Just give us your Data set.</p>
                                <!-- <p class="slider-p"> Imagine you have a Data set in JSON format, And wondering how or which graph to plot?<br>No worry, We do that for you. Just give us your Data set.
                                </p> -->
                                <a href="/graphs"><button type="button" class="btn btn-default edit-button-1">GRAPH ME</button></a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- .col-md-12 close -->
            </div>
            <!-- .row close -->
        </div>
        <!-- .container close -->
    </section>
    <!-- #slider close -->


    <!-- Service Start 
        ============================================================= -->

        <section id="service">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <div class="block-top">
                            <div class="service-header">
                                <h1>Features of Plotify</h1>
                                <p>This is a web application focusing on Data Visualizing JSON Data.</p><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- .col-md-12 close -->
                </div>
                <!-- row close -->
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <div class="block-bottom">
                            <div class="service-tab">
                                <!-- Nav tabs -->
                                <ul class="badhon-tab" role="tablist">
                                    <li><a href="#validate" aria-controls="home" role="tab" data-toggle="tab" id="validateTab">
                      <i class="fa fa-hand-spock-o"></i>
                      JSON Validation
                      </a></li>
                                    <li class="active"><a href="#graph" aria-controls="profile" role="tab" data-toggle="tab" id="graphTab">
                      <i class="fa fa-pie-chart"></i>
                      Graph From Dataset
                      </a></li>
                                    <li><a href="#collection" aria-controls="messages" role="tab" data-toggle="tab" id="collectionTab">
                      <i class="fa fa-th-large"></i>
                      Graph Collection
                      </a></li>
                                </ul>
    
                                <!-- Tab panes -->
                                <div class="tab-content edit-tab-content">
                                    <div class="tab-pane active edit-tab" id="validate">
                                        <div class="teb-icon-edit">
                                            <i class="fa fa-hand-spock-o"></i>
                                        </div>
                                        <h1>JSON Validation</h1>
                                        <p>Before we do any Analysing or calculations, We expect a Valid Json. So, Why not check your data right here. Almost the same functionality
                                            as jsonLint but it's right here.<br /> Go on, Check your JSON Data, before you we can plot your graph.</p>
                                        <a href="/validate" ><button type="button" class="btn btn-default edit-button-1" style="color:black;">Validate JSON</button></a>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="tab-pane edit-tab" id="graph">
                                        <div class="teb-icon-edit">
                                            <i class="fa fa-pie-chart"></i>
                                        </div>
                                        <h1>Give us Data, TakeAway your Graph</h1>
                                        <p> Once you submit your valid JSON dataset, we do a few magic tricks, and provide you with possible graphs which support your data.
                                            All Graphs we use are supported by <b>D3.js </b>. A Huge shoutout to D3. <br /> On click of your graph, we plot it for your dataset 
                                            and Kaboom, you have your visualization.</p>
                                        <a href="/graphs"><button type="button" class="btn btn-default edit-button-1" style="color:black;">GRAPH ME</button></a>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="tab-pane edit-tab" id="collection">
                                        <div class="teb-icon-edit">
                                            <i class="fa fa-th-large"></i>
                                        </div>
                                        <h1>Our Graph Collection</h1>
                                        <p>We give you options after analyzing the data set from our Graph Collection.
                                            Each Graph here, will give an insight of the look, accepted data, and a few data restrictions. <br/>
                                            Please stay tuned as we increase our graph support database everyday, every minute.</p>
                                        <a href="/graphCollection"><button type="button" class="btn btn-default edit-button-1" style="color:black;">See our Collection</button></a>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- .col-md-12 close -->
                </div>
                <!-- row close -->
            </div>
            <!-- .container close -->
        </section>
        <!-- #service close -->


        <script>
            $(document).ready(function () {
    
                $("#validate").hide();
                $("#graph").show();
                $("#collection").hide();
    
                $("#validateTab ").click(function () {
                    $("#validate").show();
                    $("#graph").hide();
                    $("#collection").hide();
    
                });
                $("#graphTab ").click(function () {
                    $("#validate").hide();
                    $("#graph").show();
                    $("#collection").hide();
    
                });
                $("#collectionTab ").click(function () {
                    $("#validate").hide();
                    $("#graph").hide();
                    $("#collection").show();
    
                });
            });
        </script>

      <% include templates/footer.ejs %>
</body>

</html>